title.narrative: IR 107 HEALTH FACILITIES PROVIDE HIGH IM

description.narrative: Health facilities in target districts provide high impact interventions and quality clinical services for maternal, newborn and child survival by 2015, which contributes to Child Health, Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Immunization, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children, mothers and pregnant women benefit from high impact interventions contributing to the attainment of MDG targets for child and maternal survival and development.

sector.narrative: Breastfeeding protection, promotion and support (including work on Code)

Diet diversity in early childhood (children under 5), includes complementary feeding and MNPs
Immunization supply chain, including cold chain
Measles and rubella supplementary immunization activities
